<task id="task-7549" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Clone a Git repository</title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">After enabling Git Integration, you can clone an existing
         <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Git repository</uicontrol> into a new directory on
         the local machine.<p class="- topic/p ">Do as follows:</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the main toolbar, click on the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Git</i> icon and select
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Clone Project</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">You can also click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Clone Git Project</uicontrol> in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Tests Explorer</uicontrol> section. <image width="400" href="../image/ks-pe-clone-git-1.png" class="- topic/image "/></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Clone Git Repository</uicontrol> dialog appears.</cmd></step></steps></taskbody></task>